--- Key findings ---
1. Most effective reducer (non-degraded, decrease-expected): CAA (targeted) (logit +0.126, coef -2000)
1b. Bidirectionality check: 1/4 conformist roles show a statistically significant INCREASE in sycophancy at their best (increase-selector) coefficient.
2. Assistant Axis significantly reduces sycophancy (Wilcoxon p_adj = < 1e-15)
3. Pooled projection analysis: axis projection IS correlated with sycophancy (r = -0.045, p = 2.991e-08)

